cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with robotic tasks and their adaptation through learning-from-demonstration approaches.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper leverages Bayesian optimization to endow the robot with data-efficient adaptation capabilities.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the robot's ability to understand human intended changes from noisy haptic data and adapt accordingly.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the paper may involve visual perception for the robot to interact with the environment and humans.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the control of robotic tasks and their adaptation.
